# ASP.NET Core Book Management System

A full-stack ASP.NET Core project that combines a REST API with an MVC/Razor UI for managing books.

## Features

- ASP.NET Core Web API
- MVC / Razor Views UI
- Swagger API documentation
- CRUD operations for books
- Search books by ISBN and version
- Google Books API integration
- Layered architecture
- Async API handling using HttpClient

## Technologies Used

- ASP.NET Core
- C#
- MVC / Razor Views
- REST APIs
- Swagger
- Bootstrap
- HttpClient
- Google Books API

## Project Structure

- Controllers → API and MVC controllers
- Services → External API integration logic
- Models → Data models
- Data → In-memory data storage
- Views → MVC UI pages

## API Endpoints

### Get all books

GET /api/book

### Get book by ISBN

GET /api/book/{isbn}

### Get book by ISBN and version

GET /api/book/{isbn}?version=1

### Add a new book

POST /api/book

### Update a book

PUT /api/book/{isbn}

### Delete a book

DELETE /api/book/{isbn}/{version}

## UI Features

- View all books
- Add books
- Search by ISBN
- Edit books
- Delete books

## Swagger

Swagger is available at:

/swagger

## Notes

The project integrates with Google Books API to fetch additional book details using ISBN numbers.

If Google API quota is exceeded, fallback messages are displayed gracefully.

